17/03/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Security was tightened in Sarajevo on Wednesday (16 March) after a reported security threat against the Office of the High Representative's (OHR) building.
The Federation of BiH Interior Ministry and the State Investigation and Protection Agency confirmed security measures had been upgraded, but refused to elaborate.
According to local press reports, the measures followed an anonymous threat Tuesday, claiming a truck packed with explosives would attack the OHR building.
It was evacuated for several hours but nothing suspicious was found.
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 17/03/05;
OHR Sources, Pincom.info - 16/03/05)
